{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"164eceb4-056c-4aea-b311-366c260a433e","content":"Here's what you need for automatic crash dump collection with a NativeAOT .NET 11 app:\n\n**Key points:**\n- NativeAOT doesn't bundle `createdump`, so `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` is **required**\n- `SYS_PTRACE` capability is needed for `createdump` to attach to the crashing process\n- A writable volume is needed to store dumps\n\n**Pod spec changes:**\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: my-app\n      # ... your existing image/ports/etc ...\n      env:\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"                        # 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: \"/tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t\" # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: \"/opt/tools/createdump\"     # required for NativeAOT\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add:\n            - SYS_PTRACE                     # createdump needs ptrace access\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi                       # adjust to your app's memory footprint\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- **Dump type 4 (Full)** captures everything; use `2` (Heap) or `3` (Triage) to save space.\n- `emptyDir` is ephemeral — swap to a `PersistentVolumeClaim` if you need dumps to survive pod restarts.\n- Ensure `/opt/tools/createdump` is built from the same .NET 11 SDK as your app to avoid version mismatches.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"992c1ee2-e776-49af-bc49-7c993e9a990c","outputTokens":502,"requestId":"5022:D09D:267DD5:2FF42D:69F55461"},"id":"7a5992b9-0f32-4a11-99ae-b7f655af432c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:33:30.994Z","parentId":"f60fca9f-869d-4424-9bd3-2447e0237ae5"}
